A. since the operation of maxbytes-sizeof(val) is and int minus a size_t, it will always return an unsigned number, thus the statement is always true.

B. /*we want the comparison to have negative numbers so if use typecasting using explicit conversion in the conditional statement we can fix it*/

/*here is me testing out typecasting:

#include<stdio.h>

int main(void)
{
int maxbytes = 1000;
size_t letter = 1500;
if (maxbytes - (int)letter >=0)
	printf("greater than zero\n");
else
printf("less than zero\n");
}

*/

ans:

void copy_int(int val, void *buf, int maxbytes){
	if (maxbytes-(int)size0f(val) >= 0)
		memcpy(buf, (void *), &val, sizeof(val));
5}
